{"title_page": "1993\u201394 Macedonian Second Football League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition = Macedonian Second League\n| season      = 1993\u201394\n| winners     = {{ubl|[[FK Ko\u017euf|Kozhuf]] (East)|[[FK Ohrid|Ohrid]] (West)}}\n| promoted    = {{ubl|[[FK Ko\u017euf|Kozhuf]]|[[FK Ohrid|Ohrid]]}}\n| relegated   = {{ubl|[[FK Golemo Konjari|Bratstvo Golemo Konjari]]|[[FK Tiverija|Tiverija]]|[[FK Gorno Lisi\u010de|Gorno Lisiche]]}}\n| prevseason = [[1992\u201393 Macedonian Second Football League|1992\u201393]]\n| nextseason = [[1994\u201395 Macedonian Second Football League|1994\u201395]]\n}}\nThe '''1993\u201394 [[Macedonian Second Football League]]''' was the second season since its establishment. It began in August 1993 and ended in June 1994.<ref name=\"rsssf\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.no/Macedonia/mac9394.html|title=Republic of Macedonia 1993/94|publisher=RSSSF.no|accessdate=30 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n== East ==\n=== Participating teams ===\n{{Location map+|Republic of Macedonia|float=right|width=420|caption=Location of teams in '''1993\u201394 Macedonian Second League - East'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.343056 |long=21.440278 |label=<small>[[FK Golemo Konjari|Bratstvo (GK)]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.733333 |long=22.183333 |label=<small>[[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica S.]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.966667 |long=22.766667 |label=<small>[[FK Bregalnica Del\u010devo (1926\u20132012)|Bregalnica D.]]</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.220556 |long=22.705    |label=<small>[[FK Dojransko Ezero|D. Ezero]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.316944 |long=22.561111 |label=<small>'''Valandovo'''</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.133333 |long=22.4      |label=<small>[[FK Ko\u017euf|Kozhuf]]</small> |positio