ublic of Macedonia 1993/94|publisher=RSSSF.no|accessdate=30 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n== East ==\n=== Participating teams ===\n{{Location map+|Republic of Macedonia|float=right|width=420|caption=Location of teams in '''1993\u201394 Macedonian Second League - East'''|places=\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.343056 |long=21.440278 |label=<small>[[FK Golemo Konjari|Bratstvo (GK)]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.733333 |long=22.183333 |label=<small>[[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica S.]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.966667 |long=22.766667 |label=<small>[[FK Bregalnica Del\u010devo (1926\u20132012)|Bregalnica D.]]</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.220556 |long=22.705    |label=<small>[[FK Dojransko Ezero|D. Ezero]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.316944 |long=22.561111 |label=<small>'''Valandovo'''</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.133333 |long=22.4      |label=<small>[[FK Ko\u017euf|Kozhuf]]</small> |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=42.130533 |long=21.721219 |label=<small>[[FK Kumanovo|Kumanovo]]</small> }}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.72     |long=21.793333 |label=<small>Metalurg</small> |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.866667 |long=22.5      |label=<small>[[FK Sloga 1934 Vinica|Sloga]]</small>  |position=right}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.433333 |long=22.633333 |label=<small>[[FK Tiverija|Tiverija]]</small> |position=top}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.438055 |long=22.773333 |label=<small>[[FK Horizont Turnovo|Turnovo]]</small> |position=bottom}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.203056 |long=22.575556 |label=<small>[[FK Vardarski|Vardarski]]</small> |position=left}}\n{{Location map~|Republic of Macedonia|lat=41.333333 |long=21.583333 |label=<s